## How to read this

- **The blue box in the centre** is the system being designed
  (`{{SYSTEM_NAME}}`). C4 Level 1 abstracts everything inside it as one
  box — the bounded-context decomposition lives in T1.2.
- **Person boxes (yellow)** are human roles that interact with the system
  directly. Internal staff and end users both qualify; system-of-system
  callers do not.
- **System_Ext boxes (grey)** are third-party systems the design depends
  on but does not control. Their internal model is opaque.
- **Each arrow is labelled** with the protocol or message-shape that
  crosses the boundary (`HTTPS / JSON`, `OAuth 2.0`, `webhook`, `EDI batch`,
  etc.). The label is the **integration contract**, not the business
  intent — business intent lives in the canvases.
- **BiRel arrows** are bidirectional dependencies — usually a sign of a
  Customer/Supplier or Partnership relationship at the BC level (T1.2).

